name: Paul Auster
summary: Paul Auster, the acclaimed author known for his postmodern works and experimental style, passed away at the age of 77. His most celebrated work, "The New York Trilogy," earned him widespread recognition and cemented his position as a literary giant. Auster's influence extended beyond the literary world, as he also wrote screenplays and directed films, such as "Smoke" and "Lulu on the Bridge." The news of his passing has been met with deep sorrow and tributes from fellow authors, critics, and readers alike, who recognize his profound impact on contemporary literature.

name: Marijuana
summary: The US Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA) is reportedly planning to reclassify marijuana, easing restrictions on its use and possession. This reclassification is part of a broader effort by the Biden administration to decriminalize marijuana at the federal level. The change will mean that marijuana will be treated as a less serious drug, similar to prescription opioids and cocaine. The reclassification will also make it easier for states to legalize marijuana for recreational and medicinal purposes. The DEA's move is expected to face opposition from some law enforcement groups, but it is supported by a growing number of Americans who believe that marijuana should be legalized.
